      </div>
      <div class="finding-block">
        <div class="finding-block-title">Merchant side pattern</div>
        <p class="pattern-text">Most PSE merchant forms request Full name + one identity field (Document number or Email). The 4bill-mediated merchants (bc.game, Brazino 777) show empty merchant sides — they delegate entirely to the provider. Direct integration merchants (1xbet, 20bet) ask for Bank and document fields themselves.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-block">
        <div class="finding-block-title">Provider side pattern</div>
        <p class="pattern-text">Provider APIs consistently require Bank + identity fields (Full name, Document type, Document number, Email, Phone number). This set appears in supefina.net, smartfastpay.com, and starpago flows. Simpler providers (4bill) only ask for Full name + Phone number + Email.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="recommendation-box">
        <div class="rec-title">Recommended Minimum Field Set</div>
        <div class="min-fields">
          <span class="badge-min">Bank</span>
          <span class="badge-min">Full name</span>
          <span class="badge-min">Email</span>
          <span class="badge-min">Document type</span>
          <span class="badge-min">Document number</span>
        </div>
        <div class="conclusion-text">To build a low-friction PSE flow, collect Bank, Full name, Email, Document type, and Document number. Bank selection is essential — PSE routes the payment based on the user's bank. Phone number and Address should be added only if the specific PSP requires them. City appears provider-specific and is not a core field.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

